The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development approved a 200 million-euro loan
to Urgidroenergo, a Ukrainian state-run operator of hydro
generating and pump storage facilities, the London-based lender
said today in an e-mailed statement. The loan, which will mature
in 15 years, will be used to upgrade 28 power units at six hydro
generating plants, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net  